TODO: (FROM Beta Ziliani) Hi Jason, let me give you some preliminary feedback
on Chapter 2 (the only I got to read so far, sorry!). These are presentation
details, with the only big problem being that I felt at times like I was being
thrown stuff to the face without much heads-up. But probably it doesn't help
that I'm reading it in bits, so don't mind much at this comment. About the
content, I like it. I'm aware of most of these issues, but having them
presented like this gives a nice perspective of the problem. One comment about
packed/unpacked records: MathComp decided to pack the records precisely for
this reason. I remember in a presentation of MathClasses (I can try to find
where it was if you want), Georges bashed the student of Bas Spitters precisely
for this reason, claiming MathClasses won't scale to real-world applications. I
don't know what the status of MathClasses is now, and if Georges's prediction
stands, but I thought you'll find this interesting/amusing.
